TryHackMe - Startup Room Write-up
Room: Startup
Difficulty: Easy
OS: Linux (Ubuntu 16.04)
IP: 10.48.147.37 (example - will vary)

This write-up details the step-by-step process to compromise the "Startup" machine, covering FTP enumeration, web shell upload, and local privilege escalation using CVE-2021-4034 (PwnKit) without a compiler on the target.

1. Reconnaissance & Enumeration
1.1 Nmap Scan
We begin with a basic nmap scan to discover open ports and services.

bash
nmap -sC -sV -p- -oN nmap/startup 10.48.147.37
Results:

text
